 as a nickname for a person characterised by wakefulness. Compare   Wakeman  ."]},{"name":"Watchorn","meanings":["English (East Midlands, especially Leicestershire): nickname apparently from Middle English <i>wache</i> ‘vigil, wake, watch’ (Old English <i>wacce</i>) + <i>horn</i> ‘horn’. Compare the discussion of   Wakeman  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Wakeman was born in 1380, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Wakeman, was 60 and his mother, Diana Cortwright, was 50. He had at least 1 son with Ann Wormelay. He died in 1460, in his hometown, at the age of 80."},"et":{"1380–1460":"1380–1460","1352–Male":"1352–Surnud","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","–1479":"–1479","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1403–1437":"1403–1437","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1437":"1437","1403":"1403","1205":"1205","1479":"1479","1400":"1400","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","of Cheddington, Buckingham, England":"Cheddington, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1380–1460":"1380–1460","1352–Male":"1352–Kuollut","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","–1479":"–1479","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1403–1437":"1403–1437","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1437":"1437","1403":"1403","1205":"1205","1479":"1479","1400":"1400","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","of Cheddington, Buckingham, England":"Cheddington, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1380–1460":"1380–1460","1352–Male":"1352–Décédé","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1205–Female":"1205–Décédée","–1479":"–1479","1400–